messages.content: What does the ComfyUI Default Values Manager add to the settings page?
The ComfyUI Default Values Manager adds a row to the settings page.
What happens when you click the 'Edit Custom Defaults' button in ComfyUI Default Values Manager?
Clicking the 'Edit Custom Defaults' button brings up a settings dialog screen.
How are the custom defaults applied in ComfyUI Default Values Manager?
The custom defaults in ComfyUI Default Values Manager are only applied when adding a node manually.
Will the custom defaults in ComfyUI Default Values Manager alter nodes loaded from workflows or refreshes?
No, the custom defaults in ComfyUI Default Values Manager will not alter nodes loaded from workflows or refreshes.
Will the custom defaults in ComfyUI Default Values Manager affect nodes that are copy and pasted?
No, the custom defaults in ComfyUI Default Values Manager will not affect nodes that are copy and pasted.
Where is the 'Edit Custom Defaults' button located in ComfyUI Default Values Manager?
The 'Edit Custom Defaults' button is located in the settings page of ComfyUI Default Values Manager.
What is the purpose of the settings dialog screen in ComfyUI Default Values Manager?
The settings dialog screen in ComfyUI Default Values Manager allows users to edit custom default values for nodes.
